		VALUE_DATE : T24BusinessTypes:D
			@i18n:Label (en="Start Date")
			@t24:i (align=R, inputBehaviour=F, maxLength=11, sysNumber=6.0, core=true, t24Name=VALUE.DATE)
		/* The date when the contract is due to mature.
The date when the contract is due to mature, and in the case
of Commitment contracts with no value in INT.END.DATE, the
date when penalty interest/ commission will start to accrue.
The system will ensure that the maturity date is a working
day in the country(ies) defined in BUS.DAY.DEFN.
This field represents either the final date when the
principal amount is due to be repaid or the number of days
notice required before any funds may be repaid.

Fully back valued contracts can be taken in by inputting a
date less than process date. For a fresh contract input, if
this date is less than or equal to process date all
accounting entries for creation and maturity of the deal
would be generated ONLINE. Lookup files and balances files
that hold historic details will be updated. In these cases
the contract will be assigned a CONSOL.KEY based on the
current definition on the CONSOLIDATE.COND on the date of
processing. Fully back valued contracts may have only one
single interest period and repayment of principal may only
be bullet. Back valued fresh contract is permissible only
for loan type contracts and not for commitments. No update
to LIMIT is made for a fresh contract with a back value date.

An existing authorised contract can be matured with a back
valued date. In such cases a back date that is greater than
the last schedule date may be input. Back dated maturity is
not permitted beyond the last interest capitalisation date,
last principal movement date or any scheduled event date.
Accounting entries are raised ONLINE.

If maturity date is flagged to process date all accounting
entries are raised ONLINE. STMT.ENTRY and CATEG.ENTRY
records are raised ONLINE and CONSOL.ENT.TODAY records are
raised to mature the deal during end of day processing.

