For Commitment contracts the value in this field must be
equal to or greater than INT.END.DATE.
An override will be required if the final maturity date
on a loan contract is after the value in D.D.END.DATE
specified on the relevant Commitment contract.
Cannot be changed for contracts with interest basis         "S".
Change in this field will require the redefinition of         schedules.
Input of a fixed date is mandatory for discounted or
Interest/ Commission Basis "S".
The final maturity date of a drawdown under a Commitment
must be prior to or equal to the end date of that         Commitment.
An override will be required if the date is not defined
on the HOLIDAY table.
Call/Notice prohibited for Syndicated loan contracts.
Notice period (not Call) prohibited for Accounts
Receivable/Sundry deposit contracts.
An override will be required if a Call/Notice contract is
changed to a fixed maturity contract and the appropriate
number of days notice have not been given.
Call/Notice prohibited for Commitment contracts.
Drawdowns under Commitments cannot be Call/Notice. */
