		/* The principal amount of the contract.
In order to facilitate the efficient entry of the amount, an
input feature has been provided which allows for the
suppression of trailing zeros.
e.g.       INPUT            VALUE
1T           1,000.00               2M       2,000,000.00
4.5B   4,500,000,000.00
The user may also input commas to assist in the entry of
large amounts, the system will ignore their use and
implement the amount based on the numeric input.
This field will include the impact of principal increases (or
decreases for Commitment contracts) plus the effect of
capitalised interest. It therefore provides the user with a
record of the maximum liability in relation to this contract.
In the case of Syndications this field indicates the
liability of the counterparty to the user and not to the
syndicate as a whole.
In case of Deposit type contracts with value in Mat.Amount
field, the system calculates the amount and populates the
value in this field. The user may, if required, modify the
system calculated amount either upwards or downwards. While
doing so the system performs a tolerance check on the amount
entered by the user based on the settings in LD.TXN.TYPE
table for the relevant category code. The tolerance check
could be either as a percentage on the system calculated
amount or as an absolute amount on the system calculated
amount. Beyond the permitted tolerance level an error
message would be indicated.
Validation Rules
1-14 numeric characters plus a decimal point and commas.
(Mandatory input.  Multivalue field.)
Value must be greater than Zero, unless SYNDICATE.AGT bears a
value of "AGENT".
Multiple amounts can be input for Commitment Contract types only.
If the contract is linked to a commitment the amount must be
less than or equal to the available amount indicated in COMMT.AVAIL.AMT.
If linked to a commitment the value must be a multiple of D.D.MULT.AMT.
Once the contract has been authorised this field cannot be changed. */
